Program: Great Lives
Title: Ignaz Semmelweiss
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00glw8p
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 16 May 2006
Matthew Parris talks to writer and broadcaster Frances Cairncross about her nomination of the forgotten hero of medicine Ignaz Semmelweis, who told doctors to wash their hands but was ignored. Biographer Sherwin Nuland joins the debate.